    Calculates Pareto optimality

    calc_lscps_Pareto.Rd

    Calculates Pareto optimality between two traits or landscapes Z values across morphospace.

    Usage

    calc_lscp_Pareto(x,n1,n2)

    Arguments

    x

    Oject of type 'by_Wprime' or 'kriged_surface' n1 Name or the first trait or group landscape for comparison n2 Name or the second trait or group landscape for comparison

    An object of class tibble that contains the x,y grid of points across morphospace, the trait or landscape values Z being compared at each point and the associated Pareto optimality (Ri) values.

    Robert J. Brocklehurst

    ######### data('warps') data('turtles')######### warps_fnc <- as_fnc_df(warps, func.names = c("hydro", "curve", "mech", "fea")) kr_surf <- krige_surf(warps_fnc, hull = FALSE, new_data = turtles)KrSurfParOpt <- calc_lscp_Pareto(kr_surf,'hydro','mech') head(KrSurfParOpt)######### weights <- generate_weights(n = 20, data = kr_surf) all_landscapes <- calc_all_lscps(kr_surf, grid_weights = weights) wprime_by_Group <- calcWprimeBy(all_landscapes, by = ~Ecology,method = "quantile")LscpPaOpt <- calc_lscp_Pareto(wprime_by_Group,'M','S') head(LscpPaOpt)
